            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-09 16:42:41" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a young man beyond the age of puberty, but normally before marriage</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>young man</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The person referred to as a νεανίας in {S:04402000900008} is called a {L:παῖς&lt;SDBG:παῖς:000000&gt;} ‘boy’ (see {D:9.41}) in {S:04402001200008}. This should not be understood as identity in meaning, since the person concerned could have been of such an age that either ‘young man’ or ‘boy’ was a possible denotation. In other words, the age reference of νεανίας and {L:παῖς&lt;SDBG:παῖς:000000&gt;} overlaps in Greek. In a number of languages, however, there is a much more specific and clear-cut distinction in age grading.</Comments>
